# Shared per-HOST deploy config — ONE FILE PER ENVIRONMENT.
#
# Copy this to host.config.prod.env (the VPS) and/or host.config.staging.env (the
# local QEMU VM: Server=staging-vm, BaseDomain=localhost) and fill in real values.
# Every deploy script's -Env switch picks the file; bare runs default to STAGING,
# prod must be explicit (see ../STAGING-PLAN.md). Bare host.config.env is still read
# as a legacy name for prod. This is the ONE source of truth for domain + SSH details
# per box. Every service loads it via the shared Load-DeployConfig.ps1 (merged under
# its deploy.config.json). Flat KEY=VALUE; blank lines and #-comments are ignored;
# quotes around a value are optional.
#
# KEY note on TLS: a DDNS *wildcard* (*.<BaseDomain>) only makes subdomains
# RESOLVE to this box. Certs are still issued per-name over HTTP-01 (a wildcard
# *certificate* would require DNS-01, which this setup does not use).

# --- The box ---
Server=myhost.example.com
SshUser=deploy
SshPort=22
# SshKey=~/.ssh/id_ed25519   # optional; omit for ssh defaults

# --- Domain (DDNS) ---
BaseDomain=yourname.ddns.net
AdminEmail=you@example.com
